(* ### Problem
 The adjacent sides of the decagon shown meet at right angles.  What is its perimeter?

[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);

pair[] A;

A[1] = (0,0);
A[2] = (4,0);
A[3] = (4,0.5);
A[4] = (3,0.5);
A[5] = (3,2.5);
A[6] = (2.3,2.5);
A[7] = (2.3,3.5);
A[8] = (1,3.5);
A[9] = (1,2.7);
A[10] = (0,2.7);

draw(A[1]--A[2]--A[3]--A[4]--A[5]--A[6]--A[7]--A[8]--A[9]--A[10]--cycle);

label("$12$", (A[1] + A[2])/2, S);
label("$8$", (A[10] + A[1])/2, W);
label("$2$", (A[8] + A[9])/2, W);
[/asy] The final Answer is 44
 ### Proof
 Let $a$, $b$, $c$, $d$, $e$, $f$, and $g$ be the lengths shown. [asy] unitsize(1 cm); pair[] A; A[1] = (0,0); A[2] = (4,0); A[3] = (4,0.5); A[4] = (3,0.5); A[5] = (3,2.5); A[6] = (2.3,2.5); A[7] = (2.3,3.5);
 A[8] = (1,3.5); A[9] = (1,2.7); A[10] = (0,2.7); draw(A[1]--A[2]--A[3]--A[4]--A[5]--A[6]--A[7]--A[8]--A[9]--A[10]--cycle); label("$12$", (A[1] + A[2])/2, S); label("$8$", (A[10] + A[1])/2, W); label("$2$", (A[8] + A[9])/2, W);
 label("$a$", (A[2] + A[3])/2, E); label("$b$", (A[3] + A[4])/2, N); label("$c$", (A[4] + A[5])/2, E); label("$d$", (A[5] + A[6])/2, N); label("$e$", (A[6] + A[7])/2, E); label("$f$", (A[7] + A[8])/2, N);
 label("$g$", (A[9] + A[10])/2, S); [/asy] Then $b + d + f + g = 12$, and $a + c + e = 2 + 8 = 10$, so the perimeter of the decagon is $a + b + c + d + e + f + 2 + g + 8 + 12 = 12 + 2 + 8 + 12 + 2 + 8 = \boxed{44}$.
 *)

theorem 
fixes P :: "real list \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> A. P A = sum_list A"
and h1 : "length A = 10"
and h2 : "\<forall> i < length A. A ! i > 0"
and h3 : "\<forall> i < length A. \<exists> j < length A. i \<noteq> j \<and> A ! i \<perp> A ! j"
shows  "P A = 44"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer

